<div class="containerContent">
  <img class="img-fluid" src="/assets/images/smart-casual.jpg">
  <h2 class="smart">Smart Casual</h2>
  <p>Smart casual can throw off people with its slightly vague rules. The key to smart casual wear is to dress up what you would normally wear on the weekend. Jeans are okay if paired with a nice blazer and heels. Like casual dress code, anything pretty much goes, just pretend you're meeting your in-laws for the first time (keep it relaxed, but put together).</p><br>
  <p>"This dress code calls for a just slightly dressier version of your most casual look."</p>
  <hr>
</div>


<div class="containerContent">
  <img class="img-fluid" src="/assets/images/business.jpg">
  <h2 class="business">Business</h2>
<p>Time to bust out the pumps and oxfords with your best pant suit! Business attire can range from casual to formal business wear, but all have the same core pieces. Suit pants, nice skirts, blouses, shirts, and closed toe shoes (excluding sneakers) are all acceptable. Items like jeans, sandals, short clothing or tees are not allowed for business-casual venues.</p><br>
<p>"The idea is to wear something business appropriate that also feels dressed-up."</p>
  <hr>
</div>


<div class="containerContent">
  <img class="img-fluid" src="/assets/images/formal.jpg">
  <h2 class="formal">Formal</h2>
  <p>Most people aren't required to dress formally during the week, but once in awhile you may be required to glam up. Formal wear can range in price and fanciness depending on the event. As a rule, women are expected to wear gowns or dresses with pumps or evening shoes. Men are required to wear suits and dress shoes. Cities like London and New York have the largest amount of venues requiring formal wear.</p><br>
  <p>"You aren’t expected to look as if you’re en route the Oscars, but you should still make an effort with formal attire."</p>
  <hr>
</div>
